				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sinn1sl0ken" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2019868); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2019868&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250138" alt="sinn1sl0ken" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2019868)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sinn1sl0ken" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2019868); return false;" >sinn1sl0ken</a></span> <span class="odate time_1480709648 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Dec 2016 20:14</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2702308">
									

<p>Minor typographical stuff I noticed is below! Some of it could be attributed to stylistic choices or dialogue transcription but I wanted to double check.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Show&nbsp;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>In Brig, Sub-Basement Sector IV:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Bonjour paused. &quot;Maybe. The devil's in the details with cognitohazard. We have to pick through to make her right again.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Cognitohazard to cognitohazards unless Bonjour is meant to have an accent that loses this distinction. She seems to be pretty concise and terse so it seemed out of character to me.</p>
<p>In TeleConference Room, Research Wing:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Ralph nodded. &quot;Got any wild hypothesis or interesting guesses?&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Hypothesis to hypotheses to match plurality of any.</p>
<p>In Somewhere over Canada:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Sitting in the pilot's seat, a man who knew he was named EKblad</p>
</blockquote>
<p>EKblad into Ekblad.</p>
<p>In Kumsusan Palace Of The Sun:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;As I have demonstrated before, the presence of the Stele doesn't mean I defer to your organization's every whim&quot; Kim began snapping his fingers.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I would put a period at the end of this quotation; even though grammatically I'm not sure it's necessary, it adds some hard punctuation to a forceful statement and gives the reveal a little more dramatic weight.</p>
<p>In Ryugyong Parking Garage:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;Sounds like a plan stan.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;Sounds like a plan, Stan&quot; or &quot;Sounds like a plan Stan&quot;; I think that this comes from the name Stan, it looked sort of weird uncapitalized.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Ralph pulled back a piece of opaque glass seperating the cabin from the interior, and saw to his susprise a Foundation Agent lying in the backseat</p>
</blockquote>
<p>seperating to separating, susprise to surprise.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>More productive thoughts: I enjoyed being briefly drawn back into the Manna Charitable foundation. The characters were evocative on first exposure and the backstories were enlightening. All of the deliberate quirks to the writing (alliteration, assonance, internal rhyme, etc) were entertaining to read, but sometimes if I got too caught up in looking at the structure of the words I started to gloss over what was actually happening.</p>
<p>Strong +1!</p>

							</div>

								
					
